# =============================================================================
# DEVELOPMENT ONLY â€” This file is for local development with `make run`
# =============================================================================
#
# End users (Homebrew install): Run `brief` and enter your API key when prompted.
# Your key will be saved to ~/.config/brief/config
#
# Developers: Copy this file to .env and fill in your values:
#   cp .env-example .env
#
# =============================================================================
# Required
# =============================================================================

# OpenAI API key (get one at https://platform.openai.com/api-keys)
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...

# =============================================================================
# OR Use an Alternative AI/LLM Provider
# (comment out with a # in front of OPENAI_API_KEY above)
# =============================================================================

# Custom API endpoint for OpenAI-compatible services (OpenRouter, LMStudio, Ollama)
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://openrouter.ai/api/v1

# Default model ID (e.g., gpt-4o, anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-20250514, llama3.2)
# LLM_MODEL=gpt-4o

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Provider Examples (uncomment one block by removing # in front of lines)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# OpenRouter:
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-or-...
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://openrouter.ai/api/v1
# LLM_MODEL=anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-20250514

# LMStudio (local):
# OPENAI_API_KEY=lm-studio
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=http://localhost:1234/v1

# Ollama (local - run: ollama serve && ollama pull llama3.2):
# OPENAI_API_KEY=ollama
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434/v1
# LLM_MODEL=llama3.2

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional Debug & Display Flags
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Use alternate screen buffer (clears terminal on exit)
# BRIEF_ALT_SCREEN=1

# Mouse tracking mode: all, btn, or off
# BRIEF_MOUSE=all

# Print debug output to scrollback
# BRIEF_SCROLLBACK=1

# Display tool call messages in the UI
# BRIEF_SHOW_TOOLS=1

# Enable terminal autowrap
# BRIEF_AUTOWRAP=1